iconsmaker (0.1.2-1~ppa1) noble; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release 0.1.2. No functional change to the Linux build — the
    0.1.2 release statically links the Windows C runtime (crt-static), which does
    not affect Linux; this bump keeps the PPA in step with the other channels.
  * Continues to build against the pinned cargo-1.91/rustc-1.91 toolchain.

 -- Matt Comeione <oss@ideocentric.com>  Mon, 06 Jul 2026 15:51:30 +0000

iconsmaker (0.1.1-1~ppa6) noble; urgency=medium

  * Unify the pinned Rust toolchain on 1.91 (cargo-1.91/rustc-1.91) — the single
    versioned toolchain shipped by both 24.04 (noble) and 26.04 (resolute) for
    amd64 and arm64 — so one debian/ targets both LTS releases. 1.91 still
    satisfies the dependency tree's rustc >= 1.88 requirement. No functional
    change on noble (was 1.89); enables the resolute build.

 -- Matt Comeione <oss@ideocentric.com>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 06:50:50 +0000

iconsmaker (0.1.1-1~ppa5) noble; urgency=medium

  * Blank the per-file checksum maps in vendor/*/.cargo-checksum.json before the
    offline build. dpkg-source's 3.0 (quilt) round-trip drops the vendored
    Cargo.toml.orig files, but the checksum manifests still list them, so cargo
    aborted with "failed to calculate checksum of ... Cargo.toml.orig". The
    crate-level package hash is retained.

 -- Matt Comeione <oss@ideocentric.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 22:15:00 +0000

iconsmaker (0.1.1-1~ppa4) noble; urgency=medium

  * Bump the pinned Rust toolchain to 1.89 (cargo-1.89/rustc-1.89). A transitive
    dependency (image 0.25.x) requires rustc >= 1.88, so 1.85 failed the build
    with "rustc 1.85.1 is not supported by ... image requires rustc 1.88.0".
    noble-updates ships rustc-1.89 for both amd64 and arm64.

 -- Matt Comeione <oss@ideocentric.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 21:30:00 +0000

iconsmaker (0.1.1-1~ppa3) noble; urgency=medium

  * Point cargo at the vendored sources with an absolute path
    ($(CURDIR)/vendor). The relative "vendor" was resolved by cargo relative to
    CARGO_HOME, not the package root, so the offline build failed with
    "failed to read root of directory source: .../debian/vendor".

 -- Matt Comeione <oss@ideocentric.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 18:00:00 +0000

iconsmaker (0.1.1-1~ppa2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Build against the versioned Rust 1.85 toolchain (cargo-1.85/rustc-1.85)
    instead of the archive default. Ubuntu's unversioned rustc lags upstream
    (noble ships 1.75); edition 2024 requires rustc >= 1.85, so the previous
    "rustc (>= 1.85)" Build-Depends was unsatisfiable on noble.

 -- Matt Comeione <oss@ideocentric.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 13:00:00 +0000

